question:
Find $a+b+c$, given that $x+y\neq -1$ and  \begin{align*}
ax+by+c&=x+7,\\
a+bx+cy&=2x+6y,\\
ay+b+cx&=4x+y.
\end{align*}

solution:
Since these equations look symmetric, at least on the left-hand side, we add all three together.  This gives us  \begin{align*}
&a(x+1+y)+b(y+x+1)+c(1+y+x)\\
&\qquad\qquad=x+7+2x+6y+4x+y.
\end{align*} We then factor out $(1+x+y)$ on the left and simplify the right side to get \begin{align*}
(1+x+y)(a+b+c)&=7x+7y+7, \text{ so}\\
(1+x+y)(a+b+c)&=7(1+x+y).
\end{align*}

Since $x+y\neq -1$, we know $x+y+1\neq 0$, so we can divide both sides by that term and find that $a+b+c=\boxed{7}$.

First we solve for $a$ and $b$. $$a=-\sqrt{\frac{16}{44}}=-\frac{\sqrt{16}}{\sqrt{44}}=-\frac{4}{2\sqrt{11}}=-\frac2{\sqrt{11}}$$$$b=\sqrt{\frac{(2+\sqrt{5})^2}{11}}=\frac{2+\sqrt{5}}{\sqrt{11}}$$Now we solve for $(a+b)^3$. \begin{align*}(a+b)^3&=\left(-\frac2{\sqrt{11}}+\frac{2+\sqrt{5}}{\sqrt{11}}\right)^3=\left(\frac{\sqrt{5}}{\sqrt{11}}\right)^3=\frac{\sqrt{5^3}}{\sqrt{11^3}}\\
&=\frac{5\sqrt{5}}{11\sqrt{11}}=\frac{5\sqrt{5}}{11\sqrt{11}}\cdot\frac{\sqrt{11}}{\sqrt{11}}=\frac{5\sqrt{55}}{121}
\end{align*}So, $x+y+z=5+55+121=\boxed{181}$.

Note that $$
f(x) + f(y) = x^2 + 6x + y^2 + 6y + 2 = (x+3)^2 + (y+3)^2 -
16
$$and $$
f(x) - f(y) = x^2-y^2 + 6(x-y) = (x-y)(x+y+6).
$$The given conditions can be written as $$
(x+3)^2 + (y+3)^2 \le 16 \quad {\text{and}}\quad (x-y)(x+y+6) \le
0.
$$The first inequality describes the region on and inside the circle of radius 4 with center $(-3,-3)$. The second inequality can be rewritten as $$
(x-y \ge 0 \text{ and } x+y+6 \le 0) \quad \text{or} \quad (x-y
\le 0 \text{ and } x+y+6 \ge 0).
$$Each of these inequalities describes a half-plane bounded by a line that passes through $(-3,-3)$ and has slope 1 or $-1$. Thus, the set $R$ is the shaded region in the following diagram, and its area is half the area of the circle, which is $8\pi \approx 25.13.$, so the closest integer to $R$ is $\boxed{25}$. [asy]
fill((-3,1.2)..(0,0)--(-3,-3)--(-6,0)..cycle,gray(0.7));
fill((-3,-7.2)..(0,-6)--(-3,-3)--(-6,-6)..cycle,gray(0.7));
draw(Circle((-3,-3),4.2),linewidth(0.7));
for (int i=-7; i<3; ++i) {
draw((i,-0.2)--(i,0.2));
draw((-0.2,i)--(0.2,i));
}
draw((-7,1)--(1,-7),linewidth(1));
draw((1,1)--(-7,-7),linewidth(1));
draw((-8,0)--(3,0),Arrow);
draw((0,-8)--(0,3),Arrow);
label("$x$",(3,0),S);
label("$y$",(0,3),E);
label("-6",(-6,0),N);
label("-6",(0,-6),E);
label("$(-3,-3)$",(-3,-3),W);
[/asy]

