solution:
Triangle $ABC$ has base $AB$ of length $25\text{ cm}$ and height $AC$ of length $20\text{ cm}.$ Therefore, the area of triangle $ABC$ is \begin{align*}
\frac{1}{2}bh &= \frac{1}{2}(25 \mbox{ cm})(20 \mbox{ cm}) \\
&= \frac{1}{2}(500 \mbox{ cm}^2) \\
&= \boxed{250} \mbox{ cm}^2.
\end{align*}

We have that
\begin{align*}
\frac{\csc \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\cot \theta}{\tan \theta} &= \frac{1/\sin \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\cos \theta/\sin \theta}{\sin \theta/\cos \theta} \\
&= \frac{1}{\sin^2 \theta} - \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} \\
&= \frac{1 - \cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}

Multiply all three equations to find that  \begin{align*}
\frac{a}{b}\cdot\frac{b}{c}\cdot\frac{c}{d}&=\frac{3}{5}\cdot\frac{15}{6}\cdot\frac{6}{1} \implies \\
\frac{a}{d}&=\boxed{9}.
\end{align*}

Substitute 5 for $b$ in the expression defining $a*b$ to find that $a*5=2a-25$.  Setting this equal to 9, we find  \begin{align*}
2a-25&=9 \implies \\
2a&=34 \implies \\
a&=\boxed{17}.
\end{align*}

