Then for either position of $c,$
\[\frac{c - a}{b - a}\]is equal to $e^{\pm \pi i/6}.$  Note that both $z = e^{\pm \pi i/6}$ satisfy $z^2 - z + 1 = 0.$  Thus,
\[\left( \frac{c - a}{b - a} \right)^2 - \frac{c - a}{b - a} + 1 = 0.\]This simplifies to
